text: Elden Mills (June 24, 1908 – May 9, 1965) was an American politician who served in the New Jersey General Assembly from the Morris district from 1948 to 1958. He served as Speaker of the New Jersey General Assembly in 1957. ==References== Category:1908 births Category:1965 deaths Category:Members of the New Jersey General Assembly Category:Speakers of the New Jersey General Assembly Category:New Jersey Republicans Category:People from Morristown, New Jersey Category:20th-century American politicians
